    "message_2": "To solve the given ordinary differential equation (ODE) using the fourth-order Runge-Kutta method, we'll follow these steps:\n\n1. Define the ODE: y' = f(x, y) = 2x + y\n2. Set the initial condition: y(0) = 1\n3. Set the step size: h = 0.1\n4. Calculate the value of y(0.5) using the fourth-order Runge-Kutta method.\n\nThe fourth-order Runge-Kutta method involves calculating four estimates (k1, k2, k3, k4) at each step and updating the value of y as follows:\n\nk1 = h * f(x, y)\nk2 = h * f(x + h/2, y + k1/2)\nk3 = h * f(x + h/2, y + k2/2)\nk4 = h * f(x + h, y + k3)\ny_new = y + (k1 + 2*k2 + 2*k3 + k4) / 6\n\nWe'll apply this method for 5 steps (0.5 / 0.1 = 5) to find the value of y(0.5).\n\nStep 1:\nx = 0, y = 1\nk1 = 0.1 * (2*0 + 1) = 0.1\nk2 = 0.1 * (2*(0 + 0.1/2) + (1 + 0.1/2)) = 0.105\nk3 = 0.1 * (2*(0 + 0.1/2) + (1 + 0.105/2)) = 0.11025\nk4 = 0.1 * (2*(0 + 0.1) + (1 + 0.11025)) = 0.121025\ny_new = 1 + (0.1 + 2*0.105 + 2*0.11025 + 0.121025) / 6 = 1.104375\n\nStep 2:\nx = 0.1, y = 1.104375\nk1 = 0.1 * (2*0.1 + 1.104375) = 0.120875\nk2 = 0.1 * (2*(0.1 + 0.1/2) + (1.104375 + 0.120875/2)) = 0.12650625\nk3 = 0.1 * (2*(0.1 + 0.1/2) + (1.104375 + 0.12650625/2)) = 0.13194375\nk4 = 0.1 * (2*(0.1 + 0.1) + (1.104375 + 0.13194375)) = 0.14383125\ny_new = 1.104375 + (0.120875 + 2*0.12650625 + 2*0.13194375 + 0.14383125) / 6 = 1.21474375\n\nStep 3:\nx = 0.2, y = 1.21474375\nk1 = 0.1 * (2*0.2 + 1.21474375) = 0.142974375\nk2 = 0.1 * (2*(0.2 + 0.1/2) + (1.21474375 + 0.142974375/2)) = 0.148756875\nk3 = 0.1 * (2*(0.2 + 0.1/2) + (1.21474375 + 0.148756875/2)) = 0.154356875\nk4 = 0.1 * (2*(0.2 + 0.1) + (1.21474375 + 0.154356875)) = 0.166950625\ny_new = 1.21474375 + (0.142974375 + 2*0.148756875 + 2*0.154356875 + 0.166950625) / 6 = 1.33175625\n\nStep 4:\nx = 0.3, y = 1.33175625\nk1 = 0.1 * (2*0.3 + 1.33175625) = 0.166175625\nk2 = 0.1 * (2*(0.3 + 0.1/2) + (1.33175625 + 0.166175625/2)) = 0.17213125\nk3 = 0.1 * (2*(0.3 + 0.1/2) + (1.33175625 + 0.17213125/2)) = 0.17789375\nk4 = 0.1 * (2*(0.3 + 0.1) + (1.33175625 + 0.17789375)) = 0.19098125\ny_new = 1.33175625 + (0.166175625 + 2*0.17213125 + 2*0.17789375 + 0.19098125) / 6 = 1.45630625\n\nStep 5:\nx = 0.4, y = 1.45630625\nk1 = 0.1 * (2*0.4 + 1.45630625) = 0.190630625\nk2 = 0.1 * (2*(0.4 + 0.1/2) + (1.45630625 + 0.190630625/2)) = 0.19658625\nk3 = 0.1 * (2*(0.4 + 0.1/2) + (1.45630625 + 0.19658625/2)) = 0.20234875\nk4 = 0.1 * (2*(0.4 + 0.1) + (1.45630625 + 0.20234875)) = 0.21543625\ny_new = 1.45630625 + (0.190630625 + 2*0.19658625 + 2*0.20234875 + 0.21543625) / 6 = 1.58839375\n\nSo, the value of y(0.5) using the fourth-order Runge-Kutta method with a step size h = 0.1 is approximately 1.58839375."
